 downstream (Terminal, rendering, input) is identical to the local session. Moderate frontend
 work; nothing platform-blocked (libssh2 is available on MacPorts).
 
+### 6b. Window transparency (like Apple Terminal's "Pro" theme)
+Plain window translucency works on 10.6 (unlike blur/vibrancy, which is 10.10+). It is a
+window-level effect the WindowServer composites for free — no app-side sampling of what is
+behind. Mechanism:
+- `[window setOpaque:NO]` + `[window setBackgroundColor:[NSColor clearColor]]` (main.mm).
+- Blit the frame HONORING alpha (premultiply our straight-alpha buffer and use
+  `kCGImageAlphaPremultipliedLast`, instead of the current `...NoneSkipLast` which forces
+  opacity). Our compositor already produces straight-alpha RGBA and clears to transparent,
+  so default-background/unpainted areas are already see-through once alpha is honored.
+- The opacity control is the default-background color's ALPHA in the ColorPalette (contour's
+  `opacity` config): e.g. alpha 220/255 -> ~86% opaque background, desktop shows through.
+This is the SAME premultiply change the background image (item 7) needs, and it is a
+prerequisite for it. Cheap and high-value; do before/with the background image. NB: blur is
+separate and NOT available on 10.6.
+
 ### 7. Background image
 Contour's `ColorPalette::backgroundImage` (`BackgroundImage { path-or-data, opacity=0.5,
 blur }`) is stored in the engine but was *drawn* by the deleted Qt RhiRenderer — so on this
